template=talp
#theme = my_theme 
  start_at         = wooden_room
  
  
  
  locations {
  
       wooden_room : location " You are in an <Old Room<5>>, you can see unknown <Bugs<1>> in the <NORTH<5>> side of the room! \nGo <North<5>> by clicking on <North<5>>, or typing <North<5>> or <N<5>>. " ;
       magic_grove : location " The magic is so strong here, in the <MAGIC GROVE.<5>> " ;
       inside_hole : location " You can see gems growing out of the wall \nthese <Gems<2>> are to deep to dig out, try using Examine on the <Mole<4>>, then go <South<5>> and Examine the wall\n <Deeper In The Cave<5>>" ;
       hole : location " You look down into a <Hole<5>> \nSmall bits of light spark from the hole\n If you would like to DROP an item type <DROP OBJECT_NAME<3>>\n type LOOK <OBJECT_NAME<3>> to learn about an item.\n Type <I<3>> to see what you are holding.\n";
       dead_end : location "<A DEAD END<5>> \n try <examine room<3>>, then use take <pickaxe<4>> and then get <pickaxe<4>>" ;
       gem_room: location "<Gems<3>> poke out of the walls" ;
       
       sky : location "<She<4>> has warped you out of the room and you are now on her back flying in the bright blue <sky<5>>, <she<4>> turnes and looks at you!" ;
       
       castle : location "A <Castle<5>> made from what looks like glass but, on a closer up look is clearly crystal." ;
       
       open_door : location "You enter a <room<5>>, the room is filled with <books<4>>." ;
       
       hidden_room : location "The <Hidden Room<5>> is small and smells of mold, you can feel a <draft<4>>." ;
       
       small_shaft : location "Lucky for you, that you are small enough to fit into the <Hidden Crawl Space<5>>." ;
       
       coal_room : location "You are in a <Room<5>> filled with <coal<4>>" ;
       
       fire_room : location "The <fire<4>> belows high, so high you can't tell how high." ;
   
   storage_room : location "You are in a <room<5>>, filled win <junk<4>>." ;    
   
   locked_room : location "The <Room<5>> is very small, what could be here?" ;
   
   end_room : location "The <unicorn<3>> would like you to open the locked <potion<4>> for her" ;
   
   
   
   
       
       
       
       }
       
 connections {
        from, direction, to = [ 
        wooden_room, north, hole, 
        hole, north, inside_hole, 
        inside_hole, north, magic_grove,
        hole, east, dead_end,
        hole, west, gem_room,
        magic_grove, west, sky,
        sky, north, castle,
        castle, west, open_door,
        open_door, south, hidden_room
        hidden_room, west, small_shaft,
        small_shaft, west, coal_room,
        coal_room, west, fire_room,
        coal_room, south, storage_room,
        coal_room, north, locked_room,
        locked_room, north, end_room,
        ]
        
      }
        
        objects {
        mole : scenery "an grumpy mole" start_at = "inside_hole" ;
        
        scared_mole : scenery "Running Mole." ;
        
        torch : object "A bright torch." ;
        
        potion : object "Magic potion" ;
        
        darkness : scenery "Darkness" start_at= "locked_room" ;
        
        stinky_mud : object "A hand-full of smelly mud." ;
        
        unicorn : object "Female Unicorn" start_at= "magic_grove" ;
        
        flying_unicorn : scenery "Flying Unicorn." ;
        
        gem : object "A lovely <fire<2>> red gem!" ;
        
        pickaxe: object "A strong pickaxe" ;
        
        lock : object "An old rusted lock." start_at= "hidden_room" ;
        
        broken_lock: object "A broken lock." ;
        
        book_shelf : scenery "Large bog oak booksehlf." start_at= "open_door" ; 
        
       move_bookshelf : scenery "Moved bookshelf." ;
       
       rusty_key: object "A Key covered in rust." ;
       
       light : scenery "Burning light." ;
       
       coal_wood : object "Wooden stick." ;
       
       
       locked_door: scenery "Sturdy door with a sturdy lock." start_at= "coal_room"  ; 
       
       unlocked_door: scenery "An unlocked door." ;
        
        }
        
on_startup {
      : print " <THE GROVE OF MAGIC IS CLOSE<3>>, <FIND IT AND SAVE THE UNICORN<4>>.\n type <HELP<5>> for help,\n type <SAVE<5>> to save\n and <LOAD<5>> to load.\n Do not add a <S<2>> onto the end of a word such as <GEM<4>>.\n template style is <talp<1>>\n type <QUITE<5>> to restart game" ;
      : press_any_key ;
      }
      
      ######################################
      #  On Command                        #
      ######################################
      
      on_command {
      : match "examine room"  {
         : if (is_at "castle") {
            : print_graphic "castle" ;
            
         }
         
      }
      
         
         : match "examine room"  {
            : if (is_at "hole") {
               : print "The walls of a strange <Mud<9>> on them." ;
               : print_graphic "mudroom" ;
               
            }
            
         }
         : match "examine room"  {
            : if (is_at "wooden_room") {
               : print "You see lot of <Bugs<8>> in the <North<5>> side of the room above a <Hole<6>>" ;
               : print_graphic "room" ;
               
            }
            
         }
        
         
         
         : match "examine bookshelf"  {
            : if (is_present "book_shelf") {
               : print "The <bookshelf<5>> seems to sound <hallow<2>>." ;
               : print_graphic "bookroom" ;
               
            }
            
         }
         : match "examine book"  {
            : if (is_at "open_door") {
               : print "Maybe it is more about the <BOOKSHELF<5>> then the books?" ;
               
            }
            
         }
         : match "examine room"  {
            : if (is_at "open_door") {
               : print "You see drag or <PUSH<7>> marks on the floor!" ;
               : print_graphic "bookroom" ;
               
            }
            
         }
         
         : match "examine coal"  {
            : if (is_at "coal_room") {
              : print "YOU HAVE NOTHING TO PUT THE COAL IN HOWEVER YOU SEE A <WOODEN<9>> STICK" ;
               : print_graphic "coal" ;
               
            }
            
         }
         : match "light wood;use wood"  {
            : if (is_carried "coal_wood" && is_at "fire_room") {
               : print "You light the stick, giving you a <torch<9>>!" ;
               : swap o1 = "coal_wood"  o2 = "torch" ;
               
               
            }
            
         }
         
         
         : match "examine fire"  {
            : if (is_at "fire_room") {
               : print "I am not touching that!" ;
               : print_graphic "fire" ;
               
            }
            
         }
        
        
         
         
         : match "examine mole;talk mole "  {
            : if (is_present "mole") {
               : print "\"what is that smell?\", says the grumpy MOLE" ;
               : print_graphic "moleroom" ;
               
            }
            
            
            }
            : match "examine wall;examine walls"  {
              : if (is_at "hole") {
                  : print "The walls are covered in stinky <mud<8>>!" ;
                  : print_graphic "mudroom" ;
                  
               }
               
            }
           : match "pick mud;get mud"  {
              : if (has_not_created "stinky_mud" && is_at "hole") {
                 : create "stinky_mud" ;
                 : redescribe;
                 
              }
              
           }
          :match "use mud" {
          : if (is_present "stinky_mud") {
             : print "This would make a great gift for <SOMEONE<7>> ELSE, <GREEDY<6>>!" ;
             
             
          }
          
           } 
           
           : match "give mud"  {
              : if (is_present "mole" && is_carried "stinky_mud") {
                 : print "The <MOLE<6>> sniffs the <mud<4>>, the smell is to strong and he flees in fear of the bad smell!\n <success<7>>" ;
                 : destroy "stinky_mud" ;
                 : swap o1 = "mole"  o2 = "scared_mole" ;
                 : press_any_key ;
                 : redescribe;
                 
              }
              
           }
         
              : match "unlock door"  {
                 : if (is_present "locked_door" && is_carried "rusty_key") {
                    : print "YOU UNLOCK THE STURDY DOOR!\n <success<7>>" ;
                    : destroy "rusty_key" ;
                    : swap o1 = "locked_door"  o2 = "unlocked_door" ;
                    
                 }
                 
              }
              
           
           
           
           : match "examine room"  {
           : if (is_at "dead_end") {
              : print "You see a <pickaxe<5>>" ;
              : print_graphic "pickaxe_room" ;
              
           }
           
              
           }
           
           : match "take pickaxe;get pickaxe"  {
             : if (has_not_created "pickaxe" && is_at "dead_end") {
                : create "pickaxe" ;
                : redescribe;
                
                
             }
              
           }
           
          : match "examine gems"  {
             : if (is_at "gem_room") {
                : print "If you had a <tool<5>> you could mine these <gems<2>> unlike the other rooms!" ;
                : print_graphic "gemrrom" ;
                
             }
             
          }
           : match "mine gem;take gem;get gem"  {
              : if (has_not_created "gem" && is_at "gem_room" && is_carried "pickaxe") {
                 : create "gem" ;
                 : redescribe;
              }
              
           }
           : match "get key;take key"  {
              : if (has_not_created "rusty_key" && is_at "storage_room") {
                 : create "rusty_key" ;
                 : redescribe;
                 
              }
              
           }
           
           : match "give gem"  {
              : if (is_present "unicorn" && is_carried "gem") {
                 : print "The gem glows a bright red as you hand her the gem. the ligh fills the room\n <success<7>>" ;
                 : destroy "gem" ;
                 : swap o1 = "unicorn"  o2 = "flying_unicorn" ;
                 : press_any_key ;
                 : redescribe;
                 : print_graphic "sky" ;
                 
              }
              
           }
           : match "use torch;wave torch"  {
              : if (is_present "darkness" && is_carried "torch") {
                : destroy "darkness" ;
                 : swap o1 = "darkness"  o2 = "light" ;
                 : print "success" ;
                : press_any_key ;
                 : redescribe;
                 : print_graphic "darkness" ;
                 
              }
              
           }
           
           
           : match "use key"  {
              : if (is_present "locked_door" && is_carried "rusty_key") {
                 : destroy "rusty_key" ;
                 : swap o1 = "locked_door"  o2 = "unlocked_door" ;
                 : print "success" ;
                 : press_any_key ;
                 : redescribe;
                 : print_graphic "shaft" ;
                 
              }
              
           }
           
           : match "examine unicorn"  {
              : if (is_present "unicorn") {
                 : print "She is a pearl <white Unicorn<8>>, her horn is <gold<6>> with some <gems<2>> in it, however, you can see one is missing!" ;
                 : print_graphic "grove" ;
                 
              }
              
           }
           : match "examine room"  {
              : if (is_at "storage_room") {
                 : print "You see a box of <keys<6>> on the wall." ;
                 : print_graphic "junkroom" ;
                 
              }
              
           }
           
           : match "use pickaxe"  {
              : if (is_present "lock") {
                 : print "You smash the lock, it scatters across the floor.\n <success<7>>" ;
                 : swap o1 = "lock"  o2 = "broken_lock" ;
                 : print "success" ;
                 : press_any_key ;
               : redescribe;
               
              }
              
           }
           : match "push bookshelf;pull bookshelf"  {
              : if (is_present "book_shelf") {
                : print "You push the bookcase.\n <success<7>>" ;
                : swap o1 = "book_shelf"  o2 = "move_bookshelf" ;
                 : press_any_key ;
                 : redescribe;
                 
                 
              }
              
           }
           
           : match "take potion;touch potion"  {
              : if (is_at "end_room") {
                 : print "You open the bottle for the Unicorn, she turns into the Lost Queen.\n <success<7>>" ;
                 : print "YOU WIN" ;
                 : win_game ;
                 : press_any_key ;
                 : redescribe;
                 : print_graphic "bottle" ;
                 
              }
              
           }
           : match "get wood;take wood"  {
              : if (is_at "coal_room" && has_not_created "coal_wood") {
                 : create "coal_wood" ;
                 : print "You got a <wooden stick<3>>." ;
                 : press_any_key ;
                 : redescribe;
                 
                 
              }
              
           }
           : match "examine bug"  {
              : if (is_at "wooden_room") {
                 : print "A <Bug<1>> looks deep into your eyes, and inside your head you hear.\n You now have magic!\n Save the <Queen<8>>!" ;
                 
              }
              
           }
           
           
           : match "examine potion"  {
              : if (is_at "end_room") {
                 : print "The <potion<9>> is sealed by magic, why not touch it to see if you can open it." ;
                 
              }
              
           }
           
           }
           
         
         
         
  
           
        
         
      
     
      
      ######################################
      #  Themes                            #
      ######################################
      
      #themes {
   #my_theme : theme {
      #extends = two
      #theme_settings {
        // (userfont_ will always be a prefix).
         #font = userfont_orbiter
      #}
      #screen {
         // This represents how many virtual pixels of spacing
         // to add below the baseline of the font in the status
         // bar area. Generally speaking, 2 works well for 95%
         // of ZX Origins fonts.
         #status_bar_padding_bottom  = 2
      #}
   #}
#}
      #assets
      
      assets {
          
         graphics {
            
      title : base64_png "";
      zx_venice : base64_png "";
      room : base64_png "";
      bookroom : base64_png "";
      coal : base64_png "";
      fire : base64_png "";
      moleroom : base64_png "";
      mudroom : base64_png "";
      pickaxe_room : base64_png "";
      gemrrom : base64_png "";
      darkness : base64_png "";
      grove : base64_png "";
      junkroom : base64_png "";
      bottle : base64_png "";
      shaft : base64_png "";
      sky : base64_png "";
      castle : base64_png "";
         }
         
      }
      #wooden_room =room
      loading_screen =title
      
######################################
#  Barriers                          #
######################################

barriers {

barrier_unicorn : block_path {

   from    = magic_grove
   to      =  sky
   message = The path is blocked by rubble.
   block_when_exists = unicorn
   show_blocked_exit = true
}

barrier_darkness : block_path {

   from    = locked_room
   to      = end_room
   message = The path is blocked by a door.
   block_when_exists = darkness
   show_blocked_exit = true
}


  barrier_door : block_path {
  
     from    = coal_room
     to      = locked_room
     message = The path is blocked by a sturdy. door
     block_when_exists = locked_door
     show_blocked_exit = true
     
  }
   
   barrier_book_shelf : block_path {
   
      from    = open_door
      to      = hidden_room
      message = A Bookcase is in front of you!
      block_when_exists = book_shelf
      show_blocked_exit = true
   }
   
   barrier_hidden_room : block_path {
   
      from    = hidden_room
      to      = small_shaft
      message = A rusted lock.
      block_when_exists = lock 
      show_blocked_exit = true
      
   }
   
   barrier_inside_hole : block_path {
   
      from    = inside_hole
      to      = magic_grove
      message = A MOLE BLOCKS YOUR PATH!
      block_when_exists = mole
      show_blocked_exit = true
      
   }
   
}
